%md
# Notes
* You can adjust the displayed domain, range and grouping through the settings button on a query result.
* You can do auto complete with Ctrl + . I find it does work well with __pyspark__.
* 
Visual analysis
Shows that yr_built is noisy. Pretty steady after 1970. Perhpas I can encode that.
# rooms probably good to use as # becasue it goes up nearly linearly.
# So does grade

%sql

select zipcode, round(avg(price),2), count(*) from homes where bedrooms <= ${rooms=2} group by zipcode order by 2 desc limit 15

%sql

select grade, round(avg(price), 0) from homes group by grade order by grade

%sql
select round(avg(price),0) as avg_price, bedrooms from homes group by bedrooms order by bedrooms

%sql
select price, bedrooms, yr_built, sqft_living, sqft_lot  from homes

%sql
select round(avg(price),0) as avg_price, yr_built from homes group by yr_built order by yr_built
